You are implementing a Blazor Web App shipment tracker in /tmp/sv-759de91d25b3475ca6a5b4664a3edd07/ShipmentTracker/. The project was scaffolded with `dotnet new blazor -o ShipmentTracker -int Auto -ai -au Individual`.

Project structure:
- `ShipmentTracker/` - server project
- `ShipmentTracker.Client/` - client project (interactive components go here)

The server Program.cs already has Identity, EF Core (SQLite), and Auto render mode configured.
The client Program.cs has auth deserialization set up.

## Task

Implement a logistics shipment tracking app with these features:
1. **Dispatchers** see a list of all shipments with status, destination, and can update shipment status
2. **Customers** can track their shipment by tracking number and see status + estimated delivery

### Step-by-step:

1. **Delete template pages** in `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/`: Remove `Counter.razor` and `Weather.razor`. Keep `Home.razor`, `Auth.razor`, and `NotFound.razor`.

2. **Create shared models** in `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Exception
}
```

3. **Create service interface** in `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<Shipment?> GetByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<Shipment?> UpdateStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status);
    Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment);
}
```

4. **Create client-side implementation** in `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs`:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentHttpService : IShipmentService
{
    private readonly HttpClient _http;

    public ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient http)
    {
        _http = http;
    }

    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await _http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>("api/shipments") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        var response = await _http.GetAsync($"api/shipments/track/{Uri.EscapeDataString(trackingNumber)}");
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> UpdateStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status)
    {
        var response = await _http.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{id}/status", status);
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        var response = await _http.PostAsJsonAsync("api/shipments", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return (await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>())!;
    }
}
```

5. **Register HttpClient and service in client Program.cs** (`ShipmentTracker.Client/Program.cs`):
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Hosting;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);

builder.Services.AddAuthorizationCore();
builder.Services.AddCascadingAuthenticationState();
builder.Services.AddAuthenticationStateDeserialization();

builder.Services.AddHttpClient<IShipmentService, ShipmentHttpService>(client =>
{
    client.BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress);
});

await builder.Build().RunAsync();
```

Wait — `AddHttpClient` is not available in WebAssembly. Use this instead:
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Hosting;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);

builder.Services.AddAuthorizationCore();
builder.Services.AddCascadingAuthenticationState();
builder.Services.AddAuthenticationStateDeserialization();

builder.Services.AddScoped(sp => new HttpClient { BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress) });
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentHttpService>();

await builder.Build().RunAsync();
```

6. **Add Shipment DbSet to ApplicationDbContext** - Edit `ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` to add:
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
```
and add the property:
```csharp
public DbSet<Shipment> Shipments => Set<Shipment>();
```

7. **Create server-side service** in `ShipmentTracker/Services/ShipmentServerService.cs`:
```csharp
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Data;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Services;

public class ShipmentServerService : IShipmentService
{
    private readonly ApplicationDbContext _db;

    public ShipmentServerService(ApplicationDbContext db)
    {
        _db = db;
    }

    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await _db.Shipments.OrderByDescending(s => s.CreatedAt).ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        return await _db.Shipments.FirstOrDefaultAsync(s => s.TrackingNumber == trackingNumber);
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> UpdateStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status)
    {
        var shipment = await _db.Shipments.FindAsync(id);
        if (shipment is null) return null;
        shipment.Status = status;
        await _db.SaveChangesAsync();
        return shipment;
    }

    public async Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        shipment.TrackingNumber = $"SHP-{Guid.NewGuid().ToString()[..8].ToUpper()}";
        shipment.CreatedAt = DateTime.UtcNow;
        _db.Shipments.Add(shipment);
        await _db.SaveChangesAsync();
        return shipment;
    }
}
```

8. **Create API endpoints** - Add a file `ShipmentTracker/Endpoints/ShipmentEndpoints.cs`:
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Endpoints;

public static class ShipmentEndpoints
{
    public static void MapShipmentEndpoints(this WebApplication app)
    {
        var group = app.MapGroup("api/shipments");

        group.MapGet("/", async (IShipmentService service) =>
            Results.Ok(await service.GetAllShipmentsAsync()))
            .RequireAuthorization();

        group.MapGet("/track/{trackingNumber}", async (string trackingNumber, IShipmentService service) =>
        {
            var shipment = await service.GetByTrackingNumberAsync(trackingNumber);
            return shipment is null ? Results.NotFound() : Results.Ok(shipment);
        }).RequireAuthorization();

        group.MapPut("/{id}/status", async (int id, ShipmentStatus status, IShipmentService service) =>
        {
            var shipment = await service.UpdateStatusAsync(id, status);
            return shipment is null ? Results.NotFound() : Results.Ok(shipment);
        }).RequireAuthorization();

        group.MapPost("/", async (Shipment shipment, IShipmentService service) =>
            Results.Created($"/api/shipments/{shipment.Id}", await service.CreateShipmentAsync(shipment)))
            .RequireAuthorization();
    }
}
```

9. **Register server service and endpoints in server Program.cs**. Add these lines to `ShipmentTracker/Program.cs`:
- After the Identity services registration block (after `builder.Services.AddSingleton<IEmailSender<ApplicationUser>, IdentityNoOpEmailSender>();`), add:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServerService>();
```
- Add the using statements at the top:
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Endpoints;
```
- Before `app.Run();`, add:
```csharp
app.MapShipmentEndpoints();
```

10. **Create Dispatcher page** in `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/Shipments.razor`:
```razor
@page "/shipments"
@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models
@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services
@attribute [Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization.Authorize]
@inject IShipmentService ShipmentService

<PageTitle>Shipments - Dispatcher Dashboard</PageTitle>

<h1>Shipment Dashboard</h1>

<div class="mb-3">
    <button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="ShowCreateForm">+ New Shipment</button>
</div>

@if (showCreateForm)
{
    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Create New Shipment</h5>
            <div class="row g-3">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <label class="form-label">Description</label>
                    <input class="form-control" @bind="newShipment.Description" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <label class="form-label">Origin</label>
                    <input class="form-control" @bind="newShipment.Origin" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <label class="form-label">Destination</label>
                    <input class="form-control" @bind="newShipment.Destination" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-2">
                    <label class="form-label">Customer Email</label>
                    <input class="form-control" @bind="newShipment.CustomerEmail" />
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row g-3 mt-1">
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <label class="form-label">Estimated Delivery</label>
                    <input type="date" class="form-control" @bind="estimatedDelivery" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-auto align-self-end">
                    <button class="btn btn-success" @onclick="CreateShipment">Create</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-secondary ms-2" @onclick="() => showCreateForm = false">Cancel</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
}

@if (shipments is null)
{
    <p><em>Loading shipments...</em></p>
}
else if (shipments.Count == 0)
{
    <p>No shipments found. Create one to get started.</p>
